<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74824c03-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s70508"><num value="70508">§ 70508.</num><heading> Principal office</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The corporation shall have its principal office in a United States location decided by the board of directors and specified in the bylaws, but may conduct its activities anywhere.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id74824c04-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1353">112 Stat. 1353</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/119/57/s6">Pub. L. 119–57, § 6</ref>, <date date="2025-12-12">Dec. 12, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/712">139 Stat. 712</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
